# Design system enforcer (GymBroPortal)

Treat **Figma Make (React export)** as **design reference only**, not shippable code. Implement with **Angular + PrimeNG + `src/app/shared/ui/`** per `.cursor/rules/angular-frontend.mdc` and `.cursor/rules/figma-design-system.mdc`.

## Enforce

1. **Extract the design system before implementation** — layout grid, spacing rhythm, component types (field, card, preview, chips), primary vs secondary actions. Document mentally or against `docs/design-system.md` before writing templates.
2. **No React → Angular conversion** — do not transliterate JSX, shadcn, or export file structure into `src/app/`. Re-express intent using existing app patterns.
3. **`shared/ui` reuse** — `app-button`, `app-input`, `app-select`, `app-form-field`, `app-page-header`, `app-filter-bar`, `app-data-table`, `app-ui-panel-card`, etc. Extend shared components when a pattern repeats; do not fork one-off copies in features.
4. **Tailwind spacing system** — prefer `gap-6` (sections), `gap-4` (inner groups), `p-5` (card/panel padding) unless a shared component already defines a canonical value; stay on the 8px rhythm (`gap-2`, `gap-4`, `gap-6`).
5. **Standalone components + reactive forms** — `FormBuilder`, typed models, validators in TS; no template-driven forms.

## Require

- **Layout consistency** — centered content, max-width shell (~1200px where the app already uses it); **two-column** editor-style screens: **left** form, **right** preview when the product pattern calls for it.
- **Preview pattern reuse** — match existing exercise (or feature) preview panels; extract to shared UI if a second screen needs the same pattern.

## Forbid

- **Per-screen styling** — no feature-local SCSS to “fix” one page; change tokens or `shared/ui` / `styles.scss`.
- **Inline styles** — except rare non-color dynamic values if unavoidable; never for colors or layout hacks.
- **Duplicated components** — two similar cards/fields → one shared abstraction.

## Behavior

If the **structure is wrong** (layout, component choice, spacing outside the system): **rewrite** the template to match the system; do not accumulate small patches.

## AI workflow (Cursor + Claude)

1. **Analyze:** “Extract design system from this Figma export” — layout, spacing, components, hierarchy; ignore React implementation detail.
2. **Apply:** “Use the system to implement Angular UI” — map to `shared/ui`, tokens (`var(--inv-*)`, `inv-*` utilities), and `docs/figma-workflow.md`.

